Cell.Text: I've been hearing stories about dragons. That they're back. That they can eat the sun out of the sky and freeze a man where he stands. | Have you seen one in your travels?
Travelers have been coming to Whiterun. They tell stories about dragons. | I've heard of them, but didn't think they were real. Have you ever seen one?

Node.Caption: CR14QuestStartTopic: Is there any work to be done?

Cell.Text: I envy you. Facing such a beast in combat. Smelling its blood on the air. That is what songs are sung about, Shield-Brother.
I envy you. Facing such a beast in combat. Smelling its blood on the air. That is what songs are sung about, Shield-Sister.
You are a very brave man. But I already knew that.
You are a very brave woman. But I already knew that.

Node.Caption: CR14AndTheyreSpectacular: Yes, they're real. I've seen them.

Cell.Text: A sharp mind on you. We should find out for ourselves.
That is the kind of thing Kodlak used to say. And he was right. But still, I'd like to see for myself.

Node.Caption: CR14WhoKnows: Rumors and ramblings should be ignored.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Yes! I like the way you think. There are whispers of where we might find one, too. | They say he killed twelve of the Imperial Legion and shattered their bones with his breath. | I think you and I are worth about a dozen soldiers each. We'll send that beast back where it came from.
[S] G|Well, that's one way to find out if they're real. I even know where we might find one. Lead on!
We don't all lead your life of grand adventure, Harbinger.
Not at this rate. I'll just go back to clubbing horkers and scaring the debtors.

Node.Caption: CR14ThatsYourProblemNotMine: Maybe one day you'll see one yourself.

Cell.Text: Now that was a battle!
Thank you, Harbinger.
For the glory of the Companions! For Ysgramor!
We bring honor to the Companions.
I am sorry if I disappointed, Harbinger. Still, the battle was won.
I will train better for the future.
[S] G|I'm going to stay a while. Rest among these bones. This creature honored us with its life, and I will honor it with my respect.
[S] G|You go if you want to. I've never seen bones this large, and want to make sure I remember them so I can tell the story right. | Otherwise Vilkas will just say I was making it up.
